action (clients)
 [
  [
   English: Creates a Unicode scalar from a numerical value, without checking if the result is valid.
  ]
  [
   English: It is generally advised to use the safer variant {Unicode scalar with value ()} instead.
  ]
  [
   English: Skipping the validity check can be more efficient when the value is known from context to be valid. However, the caller takes responsibility for the logical soundness of the call. Creating an invalid scalar may cause a fatal error or escape into invalid program state.
  ]
  test {ignore (Unicode scalar with value (“0”: Unicode scalar numerical value) skipping validity check)}
 ]
 (
  English: Unicode scalar with value (numerical value: Unicode scalar numerical value) skipping validity check
  Swift: Unicode.Scalar.init skippingValidityCheck (value: [numerical value])
 )
 Unicode scalar
